This paper deals with natural language inference (NLI) in the clinical domain, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks and transfer learning (cs.LG), as well as domain knowledge and external data sources (cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.IR). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
